(8, 1340, 'Nicole', 'nicolestoffman@hotmail.com', 'http://www.myspace.com/nicolestoffman', '99.233.179.89', '2009-06-18 19:40:11', '2009-06-18 23:40:11', 'Does Cat Stevens know about this?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060215 Firefox/3.0.11', '', 0, 0),
(9, 1096, 'Alan Dyer', 'alandyer@telusplanet.net', 'http://backyardastronomy.com', '208.70.62.14', '2009-06-19 01:55:07', '2009-06-19 05:55:07', 'Hi David,\r\n\r\nSo where are you planning to be July 22? I am assuming China? On your own or with a group? \r\n\r\nI prompted people to get to Shanghai, too, But then I wonder -- Can people really get into China on that short a notice -- are not visas required, passports cleared, etc that all takes time and bureaucracy? As an alternative, don\'t wait any longer to plan for where you want to be in 2010. The options for that eclipse are much more limited due to the scant landfall it makes, so available spots are filling up fast or are very costly -- i.e Easter Islanders charging the usual "eclipse rates," making money while the Sun doesn\'t shine! But in many ways its an eclipse with better weather prospects and totality just as long for most places along the path. -- Alan Dyer', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_7; en-us) AppleWebKit/530.18 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.1 Safari/530.18', '', 0, 0),
(14, 1096, 'Drew Harris', 'taazimdrewharris@gmail.com', 'http://www.drewharris.com', '60.50.13.56', '2009-07-21 23:49:09', '2009-07-22 03:49:09', 'Hello David\r\nJust had a skype with Tony and he informed me that you are in China for the big moment.\r\nWell done, and btw, great website!\r\nThe NYTimes has just posted some images, spectacular really.\r\nStay well and keep chasing.\r\nI look forward to looking at your site for updates and images.\r\n\r\nBest regards\r\n\r\nDrew ( The painter guy )', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_7; en-us) AppleWebKit/525.28.3 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/3.2.3 Safari/525.28.3', '', 0, 0),
(17, 1233, 'Alex', 'scuttaj@bigpond.com', '', '150.101.163.85', '2009-08-18 02:14:57', '2009-08-18 06:14:57', 'There was a lovely conjunction visible from south eastern Melbourne, Australia, this morning, with the waning moon just below Venus, in the clear winter dawn sky at around 6.30 am.  Some consolation for having missed totality on July 22nd from the Qiantang River Bore in China.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322)', '', 0, 0),
(18, 1233, 'eclipseguy', 'imoon@eclipseguy.staging.tunaheart.com', 'http://eclipseguy.dev', '99.233.170.56', '2009-08-18 08:45:04', '2009-08-18 12:45:04', 'So sorry you missed totality this time!  Venus/Moon conjunctions are also favourite sky events. Thanks for visiting. ', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.2) Gecko/20090729 Firefox/3.5.2', '', 0, 5),
(20, 1509, 'antony', 'antsinatree23@hotmail.com', '', '94.170.126.12', '2009-09-21 14:09:16', '2009-09-21 18:09:16', 'hey david been checking your site since the ozzy desert party yeehaa\r\n we had a party posse hit shengsi island off shanghai about 60  of us all kitted out to party well full suspense with it raining an hour before first contact but turning into broken mist for 2nd contact and we got it luckily with 5mins 54secs we had time to see it pop in and out we are making a little hd film from our trip so keep you posted it should be pretty funny stuff we were with a mad bunch hope you well mate take it easy peace and love antony', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X 10.4; en-US; rv:1.9.0.13) Gecko/2009073021 Firefox/3.0.13', '', 0, 0),
