(8154, 3074, '_eg_video_description_short', 'field_55443984c0e42'),
(8155, 3074, 'eg_video_description_short', 'Is this 1986 offering from Peter Gabriel the first music video to employ a Total Eclipse?'),
(8156, 3074, '_eg_video_description_long', 'field_554439565a880'),
(8157, 3074, 'eg_video_description_long', 'This 1986 music video for Gabriel\'s beautiful song "Don\'t Give Up\' was directed by Godley &amp; Creme, the English pop music duo that began releasing albums together after splitting from the band 10cc.  Musically, they were known for their ground-breaking production work.  But their greatest success came as the innovative directors of more than 50 music videos in the 1980s.  This video is one, long shot - and features Gabriel and Bush in a never-ending embrace as the Moon totally eclipses the Sun behind them.'),
