(8794, 3102, '_trip_report_sections_2_trip_report_section_title', 'field_554d9e3162f9f'),
(8795, 3102, 'trip_report_sections_2_trip_report_section_content', '<p style="">Some of the big boulevards and promenades and little shops are very quaint.  Donkey carts, watermelon stands, scooters, open-air markets, animals  - the kind of village character that reminds me of Turkey or even Libya.  Must be the Muslim sensibility.  I walk around for a few hours on my own taking these pictures.</p>  <figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0518.jpg" alt="chi raisin stacks" /></p> <p style="">The final product.</p> </figure> <figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0523.jpg" alt="chi raisin lady" /></p> <p style="">Cheap and delicious!</p> </figure> <p style="">Nestled beneath snow-capped peaks is Heavenly Lake - an easy day-trip from Urumqi.  Mostly a vacation spot for locals, we saw one couple getting married here.  The culture of the Uyghurs is very different from most Chinese.</p>  <figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0308_01.jpg" alt="chi heav lake" /></p> <p style="">Heavenly Lake.</p> </figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0311.jpg" alt="chi heav boat" /></p> <p style="">Across the lake, we arrive at a Toaist Temple - hike up the mountain - and take a few hours to look around.  I love temples and religious sites.  They are always the most memorable and deeply-felt of the places I shoot.</p>  <figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0322.jpg" alt="chi temple steps" /></p> <p style="">Toaist Temple.</p> </figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0329.jpg" alt="chi temple pot" /></p> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0333.jpg" alt="chi alter" /></p> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0346.jpg" alt="chi smokey roof" /></p>  <figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0385.jpg" alt="chi bread sign" /></p> <p style="">Great flat bread where ever you go!</p> </figure> <figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0386.jpg" alt="chi bread makers" /></p> <p style="">Tear off a piece with your hands and eat it while it\'s still hot!</p></figure> '),
(8796, 3102, '_trip_report_sections_2_trip_report_section_content', 'field_554d9e3e62fa0'),
(8797, 3102, 'trip_report_sections_3_trip_report_section_title', ''),
(8798, 3102, '_trip_report_sections_3_trip_report_section_title', 'field_554d9e3162f9f'),
(8799, 3102, 'trip_report_sections_3_trip_report_section_content', '<figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0434.jpg" alt="chi market stalls" /></p> <p style="">Stuffed camel anyone?</p> </figure> <figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0509.jpg" alt="chi turpan hotel" /></p> <p style="">The Silk Road Turpan Hotel.</p> </figure> <p style="">I am traveling with a few dozen eclipse chasers, most of whom I have just met.  But at the ancient citadel at Jiaohe, I spontaneously reunite with people from our chase to Libya in 2006.  Eclipse chasing is one of the few hobbies where you can run into old friends halfway around the world.</p>  <figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0448.jpg" alt="chi jiaohe wide" /></p> <p style="">Jiaohe.</p> </figure> <figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0461.jpg" alt="chi zands" /></p> <p style="">Lynn &amp; Louie Zand.  We first met chasing an eclipse in Turkey in 1999.  Now friends for life.</p> </figure> <figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0454.jpg" alt="chi jiaohe dryers" /></p> <p style="">They\'re drying grapes in those huts.</p> </figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0456.jpg" alt="chi jiaohe path" /></p> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0487a.jpg" alt="chi steps" /></p>  <figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0469.jpg" alt="chi jiaohe silhouette" /></p> <p style="">This is why I love archeological sites in remote locations.  Drama!</p> </figure> <p style="">On this expedition, we travel a great deal by bus.  It can become tedious, but it is one of the best ways to see the landscape.  In this case, the vast tundra on the outskirts of the great Gobi desert.</p>  <figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0544.jpg" alt="chi dm highway" /></p> <p style="">Closer to the eclipse with every mile!</p> </figure> <figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0566.jpg" alt="chi mustard field" /></p> <p style="">Workers in the never-ending fields of mustard.</p> </figure> <figure> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0302.jpg" alt="chi toilet" /></p> <p style="">Sorry.  Can\'t get used to it.</p></figure>'),
