(8803, 3102, 'trip_report_sections_4_trip_report_section_content', '<figure><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0490.jpg" alt="chi mtn ridge" /><p style="">We rest at The Flaming Mountains.  Stunning.</p> </figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0495.jpg" alt="chi mtn close" /></p>  <figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0498.jpg" alt="chi grotto wall" /></p> <p style="">Fourth century Bezeklik caves and Astana tombs.  Burial grounds for the nobles.</p> </figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0500.jpg" alt="chi grotto close" /></p> <p style="">The eclipse is tomorrow.  Our next stop on the Silk Road is Hami - about as remote a locale as you can imagine.  But Hami was a gorgeous, bustling town!  Not what I was expecting!  Full of sights, sounds and smells.</p> <p style=""><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0681.jpg" alt="chi hami street1" /></p>  <figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0682.jpg" alt="chi hami sellers" /></p> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0683.jpg" alt="chi hami tower" /></p> <p style="">Downtown Hami.</p> </figure> <p style="">The Hami Hotel was big and definitely ready for tourists albeit a bit dated in its decor - very old-style Soviet - dank and smoky.  I felt like I was in a 1950s war film.  Some stuff worked, some didn\'t.  We actually had to bail from one of our room assignments because of the stink.  But no matter!  We\'re not here for that!</p>  <figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0686.jpg" alt="chi huddle beer" /></p> <p style="">Eclipse chaser Jim Huddle relaxes in Hami.</p> </figure> <p style=""><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_0693.jpg" alt="chi hami post" /></p> '),
(8804, 3102, '_trip_report_sections_4_trip_report_section_content', 'field_554d9e3e62fa0'),
