(9081, 3219, 'trip_report_sections_0_trip_report_section_content', '<p style="text-align: center;">My 18th Solar Eclipse Expedition My second successfully-observed Annular Eclipse!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter" alt="dm in the field1" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00607A_01.jpg" /></p>\r\n<figure>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">This is what my Front Row Seat on the Universe looked like in Arizona in May 2012!</p>\r\n<p> <a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/arizona_location.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2708 aligncenter" alt="arizona_location" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/arizona_location.jpg" width="600" height="450" /></a>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">The region around Grand Canyon National Park is an ideal eclipse location on the Earth.  Sunny and dry.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/video/beads-in-arizona">10 minute documentary film from this eclipse</a></p>\r\n<p> &amp;nbsp;\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00092A.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2671 aligncenter" alt="DSC00092A" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00092A.jpg" width="601" height="450" /></a>The mystique of the American southwest has always called to me.  This is my first experience in the Grand Canyon, and it did not disappoint!</p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p> I decided only a week before to chase this eclipse!  Was saving my dimes for the Total Eclipse in Australia later in the year.  And even though I do nothing but globe-trot to exotic locales - it does get expensive! But I made it happen.  And I was so richly rewarded for doing so.  The <a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/video/beads-in-arizona">documentary film</a> that come out of this expedition is worth every penny it cost me. </p>\r\n'),
