(450, 5, '2008-10-13 06:10:08', '2008-10-13 10:10:08', '<strong>Development Notes.</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Need to sort out how to tackle tabbed nav in media section</li>\r\n	<li>ascertain how to pull individual media pages through into aggregator page. (look into category pull-through)</li>\r\n	<li>sort out menu cascades</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 10 - worked out method of using custom fields to store video embed codes and details.Â  This will be useful when pulling video meta data through into other pages.Â  Awesome.</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 10 - <span style="color: #999999;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><span>***need to figure out how to recurse through an array in PHP*** </span>in order to automatically grab all "vid-related" field data and spit it out in the "vid-permalink" template.</span></span> This has been accomplished <a href="http://test.rubbersuit.com/eclipseguy/media-vault/video/vid-permalink-01" target="_self">here</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Home', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '352-revision-v1', '', '', '2008-10-13 06:10:08', '2008-10-13 10:10:08', '', 352, 'http://test.rubbersuit.com/eclipseguy/uncategorized/352-revision-10', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(451, 5, '2008-10-13 07:54:38', '2008-10-13 11:54:38', '<strong>Development Notes.</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Need to sort out how to tackle tabbed nav in media section</li>\r\n	<li>ascertain how to pull individual media pages through into aggregator page. (look into category pull-through)</li>\r\n	<li>sort out menu cascades</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 10 - worked out method of using custom fields to store video embed codes and details.Â  This will be useful when pulling video meta data through into other pages.Â  Awesome.</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 10 - <span style="color: #999999;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><span>***need to figure out how to recurse through an array in PHP*** </span>in order to automatically grab all "vid-related" field data and spit it out in the "vid-permalink" template.</span></span> This has been accomplished <a href="http://test.rubbersuit.com/eclipseguy/media-vault/video/vid-permalink-01" target="_self">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>oct 11 - determined that using custom wp_query is the trick to customizing the output of the page loop.Â  This is in place on home.php currently.</li>\r\n	<li>oct 12 - discovered bug in wordpress which show up if:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>using custom permalink structure</li>\r\n	<li>using custom query to generate page content</li>\r\n	<li>showposts variable in query doesn\'t match settings in master \'read\' settings in admin panel</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe workaround seems to be making sure that the \'read\' settings agree with the showposts var in the query.  This poses a limitation to having different queries on different pages that are paginated.  It doesn\'t, however, affect non-paginated custom queries, so we should be able to work around it.  Bummer though.<br/><br/>My delicious bookmarks contain some links that cover this issue.\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>sdf</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Home', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '352-revision-v1', '', '', '2008-10-13 07:54:38', '2008-10-13 11:54:38', '', 352, 'http://test.rubbersuit.com/eclipseguy/uncategorized/352-revision-11', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(452, 5, '2008-10-13 08:43:42', '2008-10-13 12:43:42', '<strong>Development Notes.</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Need to sort out how to tackle tabbed nav in media section</li>\r\n	<li>ascertain how to pull individual media pages through into aggregator page. (look into category pull-through)</li>\r\n	<li>sort out menu cascades</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 10 - worked out method of using custom fields to store video embed codes and details.Â  This will be useful when pulling video meta data through into other pages.Â  Awesome.</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 10 - <span style="color: #999999;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><span>***need to figure out how to recurse through an array in PHP*** </span>in order to automatically grab all "vid-related" field data and spit it out in the "vid-permalink" template.</span></span> This has been accomplished <a href="http://test.rubbersuit.com/eclipseguy/media-vault/video/vid-permalink-01" target="_self">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>oct 11 - determined that using custom wp_query is the trick to customizing the output of the page loop.Â  This is in place on home.php currently.</li>\r\n	<li>oct 12 - discovered bug in wordpress which show up if:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>using custom permalink structure</li>\r\n	<li>using custom query to generate page content</li>\r\n	<li>showposts variable in query doesn\'t match settings in master \'read\' settings in admin panel</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe workaround seems to be making sure that the \'read\' settings agree with the showposts var in the query.  This poses a limitation to having different queries on different pages that are paginated.  It doesn\'t, however, affect non-paginated custom queries, so we should be able to work around it.  Bummer though.\r\n\r\nMy delicious bookmarks contain some links that cover this issue.</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 13 - <span style="color: #00ccff;">may have a solution to the </span><span style="color: #00ccff;">above!!!</span> <span style="color: #000000;">looks like setting the </span>"Blog pages show at most" setting under \'reading\' in the admin panel is a hack-y fix for this issue - pagination on pages using a custom query now seems to work. I\'ve only tested this when the query is only affecting `showposts`, but it\'s working so far.Â  Promising.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Home', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '352-revision-v1', '', '', '2008-10-13 08:43:42', '2008-10-13 12:43:42', '', 352, 'http://test.rubbersuit.com/eclipseguy/uncategorized/352-revision-12', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(453, 5, '2008-10-13 08:45:46', '2008-10-13 12:45:46', '<strong>Development Notes.</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Need to sort out how to tackle tabbed nav in media section</li>\r\n	<li>ascertain how to pull individual media pages through into aggregator page. (look into category pull-through)</li>\r\n	<li>sort out menu cascades</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 10 - worked out method of using custom fields to store video embed codes and details.Â  This will be useful when pulling video meta data through into other pages.Â  Awesome.</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 10 - <span style="color: #999999;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><span>***need to figure out how to recurse through an array in PHP*** </span>in order to automatically grab all "vid-related" field data and spit it out in the "vid-permalink" template.</span></span> This has been accomplished <a href="http://test.rubbersuit.com/eclipseguy/media-vault/video/vid-permalink-01" target="_self">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>oct 11 - determined that using custom wp_query is the trick to customizing the output of the page loop.Â  This is in place on home.php currently.</li>\r\n	<li>oct 12 - discovered bug in wordpress which show up if:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>using custom permalink structure</li>\r\n	<li>using custom query to generate page content</li>\r\n	<li>showposts variable in query doesn\'t match settings in master \'read\' settings in admin panel</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe workaround seems to be making sure that the \'read\' settings agree with the showposts var in the query.  This poses a limitation to having different queries on different pages that are paginated.  It doesn\'t, however, affect non-paginated custom queries, so we should be able to work around it.  Bummer though.\r\n\r\nMy delicious bookmarks contain some links that cover this issue.</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 13 - <span style="color: #00ccff;">may have a solution to the </span><span style="color: #00ccff;">above!!!</span> looks like setting the <strong>"Blog pages show at most"</strong> setting to <strong>1</strong> under \'reading\' in the admin panel is a hack-y fix for this issue - pagination on pages using a custom query now seems to work. I\'ve only tested this when the query is only affecting `showposts`, but it\'s working so far.Â  Promising.<br/><br/>\r\nI\'ve posted this at <a href="http://wordpress.org/support/topic/167795?replies=6#post-875258" target="_blank">http://wordpress.org/support/topic/167795?replies=6#post-875258</a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Home', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '352-revision-v1', '', '', '2008-10-13 08:45:46', '2008-10-13 12:45:46', '', 352, 'http://test.rubbersuit.com/eclipseguy/uncategorized/352-revision-13', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
