(1036, 5, '2009-04-20 19:23:49', '2009-04-20 23:23:49', 'In the Australian Outback in 2002, the Total Eclipse happened just before sunset. When the Sun hit the western horizon, the Moon was still in the way! This was a once-in-a-lifetime experience. Check it ou', ' Eclipsed Sun Sets!', 0, 'Watch an eclipsed sun set! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '658-revision-3', '', '', '2009-04-20 19:23:49', '2009-04-20 23:23:49', '', 658, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/658-revision-3', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1037, 5, '2009-04-20 19:20:51', '2009-04-20 23:20:51', 'In this clip from the Total Eclipse of December 2002 in the Outback, I have modified the speed and contrast in order to accentuate the movement of the Moon\'s shadow across the Earth. You don\'t get to see the Moon\'s umbra move like this everyday!', ' Shadowdance', 0, 'Killer animation of the Moon\'s shadow sweeping through the sky! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '654-revision-3', '', '', '2009-04-20 19:20:51', '2009-04-20 23:20:51', '', 654, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/654-revision-3', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1038, 5, '2009-04-20 19:16:01', '2009-04-20 23:16:01', 'The "Diamond Ring" phase of a Total Eclipse signals the beginning of totality, and the end of totality. You get two Diamond Rings every eclipse! Watch both in this clip from the Total Eclipse in Zambia, Africa in 2001.', 'Africa Diamonds', 0, 'Watch two Diamond Rings in Zambia, Africa in 2001.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '649-revision-3', '', '', '2009-04-20 19:16:01', '2009-04-20 23:16:01', '', 649, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/649-revision-3', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1039, 5, '2009-04-20 19:10:49', '2009-04-20 23:10:49', 'Follow the handy-work of famous Canadian eclipse chaser Andreas Gada as he opens the iris on the Total Eclipse of 1979 in Gimli, Manitoba. This is some of the only 16mm eclipse film you will ever see! Killer!', '16mm Eclipse film from 1979', 0, 'More sweet 16mm film from 1979!', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '608-revision-7', '', '', '2009-04-20 19:10:49', '2009-04-20 23:10:49', '', 608, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/608-revision-7', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1040, 5, '2009-04-20 19:04:01', '2009-04-20 23:04:01', 'In this fast-motion, wide-angle shot of the eclipse in Yiwu, China, in 2008, we can clearly see the shadow of the Moon sweep across the Earth towards us - bathe us in its unearthly light - then sweep away from us at over 3000 kilometers per hour. You rarely get to see umbral action like this! Spine-tingling!', 'Umbral Action!', 0, 'Watch the umbra move across Earth! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '635-revision-3', '', '', '2009-04-20 19:04:01', '2009-04-20 23:04:01', '', 635, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/635-revision-3', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1041, 5, '2009-04-20 19:00:53', '2009-04-20 23:00:53', 'Eclipse in China - 01 August 2008. This is only a preview of the complete film which I have not finished yet! But the eclipse sequence is so dramatic I want to share it now. The clouds that threatened to eclipse the eclipse actually provided an ideal platform under which to observe the full motion of the umbra through the sky. Stunning! Don\'t miss the time-lapse version of this shot as well, "Umbral Action."', 'Shadow On The Silk Road', 0, 'Amazing eclipse action in China!', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '631-revision-3', '', '', '2009-04-20 19:00:53', '2009-04-20 23:00:53', '', 631, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/631-revision-3', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1042, 5, '2009-04-19 19:45:55', '2009-04-19 23:45:55', 'My friend Jim Huddle shot this amazing footage of the Total Eclipse in Antarctica in November 2003. From his location, the eclipse happened right on the horizon making this eclipse unique in the experience of eclipse chasers. I was in Antarctica as well for this one, but at a different location. Together, we were among the first humans to witness a Total Eclipse from Antarctica.', 'Antarctica Total Eclipse 2003', 0, 'It looks fake but this is real!!!!  Totality in Antarctica.  ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '618-revision-3', '', '', '2009-04-19 19:45:55', '2009-04-19 23:45:55', '', 618, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/618-revision-3', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1043, 5, '2009-04-19 19:17:21', '2009-04-19 23:17:21', 'Watch the change in light on the beach as the Moon\'s shadow departs our location at Baby Beach in Aruba in 1998.', 'The Umbra Retreats in Aruba', 0, 'Watch the Umbra retreat in Aruba in 1998.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '614-revision-3', '', '', '2009-04-19 19:17:21', '2009-04-19 23:17:21', '', 614, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/614-revision-3', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1044, 5, '2009-04-20 19:05:45', '2009-04-20 23:05:45', 'The Total Eclipse of 1991 over Hawaii, Mexico and Central America was considered "The Big One" because the duration of totality was one of the longest of the 20th century. This eclipse is also considered to be the one that launched the modern day phenomenon known as "eclipse chasing" when in fact people have been flocking to see Total Solar Eclipses for centuries. Famous Canadian eclipse photographer Andreas Gada shot this 16mm film from Baja California. It don\'t get no betta!!! Sweeeet!!!', 'The Big One 1991', 0, 'Sweet 16mm eclipse film from The Big One!', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '604-revision-4', '', '', '2009-04-20 19:05:45', '2009-04-20 23:05:45', '', 604, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/604-revision-4', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1045, 5, '2009-04-20 19:09:44', '2009-04-20 23:09:44', 'Thanks to NASA\'s public service, these images of the Total Eclipse from Turkey in 1999 show great chromosphere and a few stunning moments of the inner corona.Â  Check it out!Â  No audio on this one.', 'Totality in Turkey 1999', 0, 'Great shots of the corona courtesy of NASA! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '600-revision-4', '', '', '2009-04-20 19:09:44', '2009-04-20 23:09:44', '', 600, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/600-revision-4', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1046, 5, '2009-04-20 19:08:16', '2009-04-20 23:08:16', 'Watch me on the news in South Australia talking        about the Moon\'s shadow over Lyndhurst on December 4, 2002.', 'Eclipseguy in the news in Australia!', 0, 'Catch me on the news in Australia! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '595-revision-5', '', '', '2009-04-20 19:08:16', '2009-04-20 23:08:16', '', 595, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/595-revision-5', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
