henomenon around me seems absurd now.Â  Ever since that day in Mexico in 1991 I have been partnering with the universe.Â  I step out of the way with all my ridiculous, repetitive thinking, pointless anxieties and fears and unexamined concepts and I let the pure force of life express itself through me.Â  This way, none of it is mine.Â  And if none of it is mine, I have no sense of ownership.Â  And with no ownership I am free from any suffering that things aren\'t turning out the way they should.Â  I am just a wave on an ocean that knows it is not a wave.Â  I am the ocean.\r\n\r\nThis is a much better way to live than remaining in the dream world I lived in before.Â  The one where my concept of myself was limited to the boundary of my skin - limited to the flow of thoughts in my mind - limited to what I was told I was growing up.Â  This is a very false, incomplete identity.Â  One I am very pleased to have left behind.\r\n\r\nYou could say I saw myself in the eclipse that day.Â  I didn\'t know it at the time but the eclipse - which I described as sublime, enormous, spectacular - was actually a mirror in the sky that showed me the parts of myself that could also be described this way.Â  Because whether we realize it or not, each of us lives out an aspect of our lives on a grander scale.Â  Like a hologram, a fragment within us reflects the whole source that we come from.Â  We respond to the great stories of the Hero and Heroine - the Academic or the Artist - the Sex Symbol or the Superstar. The great mythological and archetypal powers are part of our psychology.Â  These collective energies are why we all respond to the things that seem larger than life - works of art - great athletes - prolific musicians and artists.Â  There is something in each of these that represent us in some way.Â  Something bigger, grander than how we appear.Â  This expanded or \'cosmic\' Self that is shared is a reality for everyone.\r\n\r\nNow - you don\'t have to become an eclipse chaser to figure this out.Â  But just in case... here is my website.', 'About', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-22', '', '', '2009-05-23 16:27:23', '2009-05-23 20:27:23', '', 2, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/2-revision-22', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
