(1267, 5, '2009-06-02 22:52:52', '2009-06-03 02:52:52', 'My girlfriend and I are travelling on our own throughout China in July.  We will observe the eclipse from southwest of Shanghai. Exactly where I haven\'t figured out yet.  \r\n\r\nBut I will be giving a presentation at Naked Retreats in Moganshan - a few hours drive outside of Shanghai on 21 July 2009.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.nakedretreats.cn" target=_blank">Naked Retreats</a>\r\n\r\nIf you are in the area stop by to say hello!\r\n\r\n<a href="mailto:imoon@eclipseguy.staging.tunaheart.com">imoon@eclipseguy.staging.tunaheart.com</a>', 'My plans for the eclipse in July ', 0, 'If you are in the Moganshan area in July - come say hello!', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1188-revision-6', '', '', '2009-06-02 22:52:52', '2009-06-03 02:52:52', '', 1188, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/1188-revision-6', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1268, 5, '2009-06-01 14:02:07', '2009-06-01 18:02:07', '<p style="text-align: right;"><img class="alignleft" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/tim_shot.jpg" alt="dm photo" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">I have been obsessed by Total Solar Eclipses (TSEs) ever since I saw my first one in Baja, Mexico, in 1991.  Since that day, I have chased eclipses of all kinds to every corner of the globe - from India to Brazil, Antarctica to Libya.  I am constantly planning wondrous and exotic adventures to stand in the shadow of the Moon and have a big desire to share the experience!  If you haven\'t seen a TSE yet, you don\'t know what you are missing.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Based in Toronto, Canada, I am a filmmaker by trade.  I run a small business and make my living directing, filming and editing television and video projects.  The eclipse expeditions are perfect in that they allow me to blend my passion for film and adventure travel into one mind-blowing experience of the world.  Don\'t miss all the killer film and video on this site!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Living life so fully, so passionately, has been a true gift.  I am one of the luckiest people on Earth to have discovered something so enormous, so inspiring that it has changed the course of my life.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">As a result, I live life on the fringe - outside the mainstream.  Whether it is my career as an independent artist or my deep passion for chasing eclipses, everything I do is unconventional.  The choices I have made in my life baffle some people.  But I know who I am.  And I will go my own way no matter the cost.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">I am heavily into music - cosmology - metaphysics - and art of all kinds.  I have gazillions of friends all over the world and value celebration, self-expression and community above all else. That\'s right - a bit of a bohemian.  When I am not chasing eclipses, playing guitar or reading, you can find me at Burning Man, at a yoga class or camping for the summer solstice.</p>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignright" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/portrait.jpg" alt="dm portrait" />\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This website is my rant on the internet about how you - yes you, right there -Â  should see at least one Total Solar Eclipse before you die. To live your entire life and never realize the power and beauty of the universe in which you live is a shame! Believe me - most people will settle for a mediocre, programmatic existence.Â  Don\'t be one of them!Â  Get pumped!Â  Life is so fleeting!Â  Quit waiting for someone to fire the starting gun!Â  Waking up to the truth about the universe, the world and yourself is the stuff life is made of.Â  But opening the eyes takes passion, curiosity and a willingness to take risks.Â  All things that are living inside of you already.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Remember: you are much more than you have been lead to believe.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Watch the videos.Â  Read the Trip Reports.Â  Get inspired and comment on anything you see.Â  You have just stumbled across the hidden world of eclipse chasers.Â  And we want you to join us.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">You must see a TSE at least once before you die!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>', 'About Eclipseguy', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-40', '', '', '2009-06-01 14:02:07', '2009-06-01 18:02:07', '', 2, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/2-revision-40', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
