(1434, 5, '2009-05-22 22:46:47', '2009-05-23 02:46:47', 'In this fast-motion, wide-angle shot of the eclipse in Yiwu, China, in 2008, we can clearly see the shadow of the Moon sweep across the Earth towards us - bathe us in its unearthly light - then sweep away from us at over 3000 kilometers per hour. You rarely get to see umbral action like this! Spine-tingling!', 'Umbral Action!', 0, 'Watch the umbra move across Earth! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '635-revision-4', '', '', '2009-05-22 22:46:47', '2009-05-23 02:46:47', '', 635, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/635-revision-4', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
