d States.', 'Eclipse Calendar', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '551-revision-37', '', '', '2009-08-06 17:57:43', '2009-08-06 21:57:43', '', 551, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/551-revision-37', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1548, 5, '2009-08-06 18:18:55', '2009-08-06 22:18:55', '<p style="text-align: center;">Animation of the Total Solar Eclipse of 11 July 2010</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2010jul11t.gif" alt="" /></p>\r\n\r\nYou have to get into that little black dot!! \r\n\r\nThis is the next major Total Eclipse to come to Earth.  It is visible almost entirely from the Pacific Ocean ONLY!  It makes landfall on a few, remote islands near Tahiti - and on Easter Island, of all places.  Many cruises to see totality have been planned and many are already fully booked.  This is an expensive eclipse to chase because of the difficult location. But what is money for?  \r\n\r\nI will provide a list of expeditions soon.  \r\n\r\nFor more on this eclipse, visit Fred Espenak\'s dedicated NASA web page <a href="http://eclipse.gsfc.nasa.gov/SEmono/TSE2010/TSE2010.html"target="-blank">here.</a>  \r\n\r\n ', 'Total Solar Eclipse of 11 July 2010', 0, 'Details of upcoming annular.  ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1521-revision-14', '', '', '2009-08-06 18:18:55', '2009-08-06 22:18:55', '', 1521, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/1521-revision-14', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
