(1552, 5, '2009-08-06 18:28:10', '2009-08-06 22:28:10', '<p style="text-align: center;">Animation of the Total Solar Eclipse of 11 July 2010</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2010jul11t.gif" alt="" /></p>\r\n\r\nYou have to get into that little black dot!! \r\n\r\nThis is the next major Total Eclipse to come to Earth.  It is visible almost entirely from the Pacific Ocean ONLY!  It makes landfall on a few, remote islands near Tahiti - and on Easter Island, of all places.  Many cruises to see totality have been planned and many are already fully booked.  This is an expensive eclipse to chase because of the difficult location. But what is money for?  \r\n\r\nI will provide a list of expeditions soon.  \r\n\r\nFor more on this eclipse, visit Fred Espenak\'s dedicated NASA web page <a href="http://eclipse.gsfc.nasa.gov/SEmono/TSE2010/TSE2010.html"target="-blank">here.</a>  \r\n\r\n ', 'Total Solar Eclipse of 11 July 2010', 0, 'This is the next big one! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1521-revision-17', '', '', '2009-08-06 18:28:10', '2009-08-06 22:28:10', '', 1521, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/1521-revision-17', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1553, 5, '2009-08-06 17:51:42', '2009-08-06 21:51:42', 'Preliminary Report - Total Eclipse of 22 July 2009.\r\n\r\nI have just returned home after chasing the eclipse to China once again.  And while this trip was much better than last year\'s expedition, we were plagued with bad weather on eclipse day.  Across eastern China, thousands of chasers pulled all-nighters and bit their nails down to the skin watching the satellite images cast doom and gloom on our hopes of clear skies.  Just hours before the eclipse began, I decided there was no clear advantage to running, and we stayed at Naked Retreats in Moganshan to try our luck.  And while Shanghai was drenched with rain, and other "best sites" were completely clouded out, we experienced one of the most dramatic eclipses of the last 20 years.  Through blankets of rolling mist and fog we caught multiple glimpses of totality through holes in the sky.  The video is awesome!  Just goes to show that while clear skies is what you hope for, nature will always surprize you with its wonders.  Not what I was expecting - but completely satisfied.  \r\n\r\nWhile I prepare my images and video for the complete report, check out these links: \r\n\r\nSam Beattie from Agence France-Presse followed me to Moganshan for the eclipse and filed this video report: \r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/video/canadas-eclipse-chaser/article1227034/"target="-blank">The Globe & Mail</a>\r\n\r\nOther images from across the eclipse path: \r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/krisdelcourte/sets/72157621822513677/show/"target="-blank">Mr. Black Sun</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.boston.com/bigpicture/2009/07/the_longest_solar_eclipse_of_t.html"target="-blank">The Boston Globe</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://s10.photobucket.com/albums/a120/alsonwong/China%202009/?action=view&current=DSC_0002Crop800.jpg"target="-blank">Alson Wong Images</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://spaceweather.com/eclipses/gallery_22jul09.htm"target="-blank">Space Weather</a>\r\n', 'The Misty Eclipse!  ', 0, 'Through blankets of rolling mist and fog we witnessed the grand Total Eclipse of 2009. Read the preliminary report.  ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1509-revision-14', '', '', '2009-08-06 17:51:42', '2009-08-06 21:51:42', '', 1509, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/1509-revision-14', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1554, 5, '2009-06-08 15:38:18', '2009-06-08 19:38:18', 'The shadow of the Moon visits Earth next on 22 July 2009.\r\n\r\nWhere will you be?Â  Sitting at home?Â  At work?Â  Wasting time watching TV?\r\n\r\nForget all that.Â  Book a flight to Shanghai right now.Â  Come and see your first Total Solar Eclipse.\r\n<figure><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/TSE2009globe_400.jpg" alt="TSE2009_globe" />\r\nThe dark blue line is where you can see a Total Eclipse. Best place to see it is China.</figure>\r\n<figure><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/TSE2009_china_path.jpg" alt="TSE2009_path" />\r\n\r\nThis is the eclipse path through China.  Pick a city!  Let\'s go!\r\n\r\nImages Espenak/NASA/GSFC</figure>\r\nQuit wasting so much time.  Contact me immediately to get on an expedition - last minute!\r\n\r\n<a href="mailto:imoon@eclipseguy.staging.tunaheart.com">imoon@eclipseguy.staging.tunaheart.com</a>\r\n\r\nOr, post a comment right here!\r\n\r\nRemember:  Quit wasting your time not seeing a Total Solar Eclipse.', 'Total Solar Eclipse Only Days Away!', 0, 'Attention all readers! This is the longest TSE of this century!  You will never get this chance again!\r\nQuit wasting so much time... ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1096-revision-25', '', '', '2009-06-08 15:38:18', '2009-06-08 19:38:18', '', 1096, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/1096-revision-25', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
