(1666, 5, '2010-01-16 02:14:52', '2010-01-16 06:14:52', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/ase2010globe1a.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1669 aligncenter" title="ase2010globe1a" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/ase2010globe1a-300x225.jpg" alt="ase2010globe1a" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\r\n\r\n<figure>In red the path of the Annular Eclipse.</figure>\r\n<a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/2010_annular_eclipse_1000.jpg"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-1667 alignleft" title="2010_annular_eclipse_1000" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/2010_annular_eclipse_1000-150x150.jpg" alt="2010_annular_eclipse_1000" width="150" height="150" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis is what you would have seen in the sky on 15 January 2010 if you were anywhere in the path of annularity.  I wasn\'t - saving for July!! But thousands gathered along the eclipse path to see the millennium\'s longest eclipse.\r\n\r\nIf you missed it, here are a few photos of what you didn\'t see.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.spaceweather.com/eclipses/gallery_15jan10.htm" target="_blank">Space Weather</a>', 'Annular Eclipse on January 15 Successfully Observed!', 0, 'This was the longest eclipse for over a thousand years!! ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'spectacular-annular-eclipse-in-january-2010', '', '', '2011-07-20 16:40:43', '2011-07-20 20:40:43', '', 0, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/?p=1666', 0, 'post', '', 0),
