(1704, 5, '2011-07-20 16:40:11', '2011-07-20 20:40:11', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/ase2010globe1a.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1669 aligncenter" title="ase2010globe1a" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/ase2010globe1a-300x225.jpg" alt="ase2010globe1a" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\n\n<figure>In red the path of the Annular Eclipse.</figure>\n<a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/2010_annular_eclipse_1000.jpg"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-1667 alignleft" title="2010_annular_eclipse_1000" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/2010_annular_eclipse_1000-150x150.jpg" alt="2010_annular_eclipse_1000" width="150" height="150" /></a>\n\nThis is what you would have seen in the sky on 15 January 2010 if you were anywhere in the path of annularity.  I wasn\'t - saving for July!! But thousands gathered along the eclipse path to see the millennium\'s longest eclipse.\n\nIf you missed it, here are a few links to photos and reports:\n\n<a href="http://www.spaceweather.com/eclipses/gallery_15jan10.htm" target="_blank">Space Weather</a>\n<a href="http://eclipse.gsfc.nasa.gov/SEmono/ASE2010/ASE2010.html" target="_blank">NASA Eclipse Website</a>', 'Annular Eclipse on January 15 Successfully Observed!', 0, 'This was the longest eclipse for over a thousand years!! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1666-autosave', '', '', '2011-07-20 16:40:11', '2011-07-20 20:40:11', '', 1666, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/1666-autosave', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
