(1706, 5, '2009-12-30 01:36:39', '2009-12-30 05:36:39', 'On 11 July 2010, a Total Solar Eclipse will be visible from a long corridor that spans the southern Pacific Ocean.  Tahiti will be teeming with eclipse seekers and adventurers taking to the sea in cruise liners and boarding flights to remote Tuamotu Islands.  Easter Island will also be packed to its shores with human eyes looking skyward.\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Animation of the Total Solar Eclipse of 11 July 2010</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2010jul11t.gif" alt="" /></p\r\n\r\nBut at the end of the eclipse day, the Moon\'s shadow crosses extreme southern Chile where an organization called Eclipse-City will operate a private charter to fly into the path of the eclipse in mid air and intercept the shadow at  35, 000 feet.  I have two rows booked on this flight.  Each row has two people sharing the window where the eclipse will be visible above Earth\'s western horizon.  As of 30 December 2009, I have one seat available in the row where the plane\'s wing will be visible.  The wing creates no blind spot for the eclipse itself, but obviously removes a portion of the sky from view.  These are the least expensive seats on the aircraft, with the "no wing" seats costing the most.  This seat is available now for €499/USD715. If you are interested, post a comment here or contact me by email.  This seat will not be available for long! \r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.eclipse-city.com/eclipse,patagonia,10087.html" target="-blank">Eclipse City</a>\r\n<a href=\'http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/091218_observation-flight.pdf\'>Download Seating Plan</a>\r\n\r\nYou have to get yourself to El Calafate, Argentina, by 11 July 2010.\r\n\r\nWith South Pacific cruises either cost-prohibitive or completely sold out, and Easter Island already packed to the rafters, this is definitely the most exciting and cost-effective option left.  And you don\'t have to worry about the weather!  This flight will travel well above any threatening clouds and we are guaranteed a spectacular observation in crystal clear skies.\r\n\r\nYou must see a Total Eclipse of the Sun from the air before you die!  ', 'ONE SEAT AVAILABLE! Eclipse Observation Flight/Patagonia/July 2010.', 0, 'I have one seat available on an exclusive eclipse observation flight from Patagonia, 11 July 2010.  Come see an eclipse with me!  Goes to the first caller!  ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1636-revision-22', '', '', '2009-12-30 01:36:39', '2009-12-30 05:36:39', '', 1636, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/1636-revision-22', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
