(2426, 5, '2009-05-22 22:37:28', '2009-05-23 02:37:28', 'Part of my awesome eclipse chase to Libya in 2006 included bounding over orange sand dunes in 4x4s and camping in the desert with hardened local guides. Thought you might like to see what the Sahara Desert looks like - up close.', 'Desert Trek Sahara', 0, 'You have never seen the Sahara Desert like this. ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '978-revision-v1', '', '', '2009-05-22 22:37:28', '2009-05-23 02:37:28', '', 978, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/978-revision-3', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2427, 5, '2009-05-22 22:38:24', '2009-05-23 02:38:24', 'Enroute to the 2006 Total Eclipse in the Sahara Desert, eclipse chasers passed through the mystical city of Tripoli and some of the best-preserved Roman ruins in the world.', 'Tripoli & The Ruins', 0, 'Never in a million years did I ever think I would be filming in Libya at some of the best preserved ruins in the world.  ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '975-revision-3', '', '', '2009-05-22 22:38:24', '2009-05-23 02:38:24', '', 975, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/975-revision-3', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2428, 5, '2009-05-22 22:39:08', '2009-05-23 02:39:08', 'After the TSE in Zambia in June, 2001, I went on Safari in Malawi.  This clip is from the half-hour film I produced about the expedition.  ', 'Malawi Safari', 0, 'A life-long dream to go on safari in Africa comes true in 2001.  Eclipses rule.  ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '971-revision-3', '', '', '2009-05-22 22:39:08', '2009-05-23 02:39:08', '', 971, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/971-revision-3', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2429, 5, '2009-05-22 22:40:11', '2009-05-23 02:40:11', 'While most cameras are pointed at the sky during a Total Eclipse, the best way to get a sense of what it feels like to be there is to witness what is happening to the people on the ground. In this clip, watch as the Moon\'s shadow arrives, then retreats, from our observing spot - an ancient archeological site 1,000 feet above the Tigris River in Southern Turkey. So killer!', 'Darkness in Turkey 1999', 0, 'One of the best ways to get a sense of a Total Eclipse is not to watch the sky... but watch the people on the ground! Daytime turns into night before your eyes!', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '967-revision-3', '', '', '2009-05-22 22:40:11', '2009-05-23 02:40:11', '', 967, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/967-revision-3', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2430, 5, '2009-05-22 22:40:59', '2009-05-23 02:40:59', 'During the eclipse expedition to China in 2008, we passed through the city of Xi\'an and had the chance to see the famous Terracotta Warriors. More than 8,000 warriors, horses and chariots have been uncovered.  They were created in 246 BC but not discovered until 1974. My invitation into the private area in the facility to film the warriors that are being repaired allowed me to get amazing, close up pictures of these sculptures.  ', 'The Terracotta Warriors', 0, 'The magnificent Terracotta Warriors!  Unique, behind-the-scenes footage - rarely seen like this. ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '958-revision-7', '', '', '2009-05-22 22:40:59', '2009-05-23 02:40:59', '', 958, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/958-revision-7', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2431, 5, '2009-06-03 09:32:39', '2009-06-03 13:32:39', 'In the Australian Outback in 2002, the Total Eclipse happened just before sunset. When the Sun hit the western horizon, the Moon was still in the way! This was a once-in-a-lifetime experience. Thanks to Klipsi for sharing his killer video.', ' Eclipsed Sun Sets!', 0, 'Watch an eclipsed sun set! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '658-revision-5', '', '', '2009-06-03 09:32:39', '2009-06-03 13:32:39', '', 658, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/658-revision-5', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2432, 5, '2009-06-03 09:33:09', '2009-06-03 13:33:09', 'In this clip from the Total Eclipse of December 2002 in the Outback, I have modified the speed and contrast in order to accentuate the movement of the Moon\'s shadow across the Earth. You don\'t get to see the Moon\'s umbra move like this everyday! Thanks to Klipsi for sharing his killer video.', ' Shadowdance', 0, 'Killer animation of the Moon\'s shadow sweeping through the sky! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '654-revision-5', '', '', '2009-06-03 09:33:09', '2009-06-03 13:33:09', '', 654, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/654-revision-5', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2433, 5, '2009-05-22 22:44:32', '2009-05-23 02:44:32', 'The "Diamond Ring" phase of a Total Eclipse signals the beginning of totality, and the end of totality. You get two Diamond Rings every eclipse! Watch both in this clip from the Total Eclipse in Zambia, Africa in 2001.', 'Africa Diamonds', 0, 'Watch two Diamond Rings in Zambia, Africa in 2001.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '649-revision-4', '', '', '2009-05-22 22:44:32', '2009-05-23 02:44:32', '', 649, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/649-revision-4', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2434, 5, '2010-04-10 10:36:45', '2010-04-10 14:36:45', 'Follow the handy-work of famous Canadian eclipse chaser Andreas Gada as he opens the iris on the Total Eclipse of 1980 in Voi, Kenya. This is some of the only 16mm eclipse film you will ever see! Killer!', '16mm Eclipse film from 1980', 0, 'More sweet 16mm film from 1980!', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '608-revision-10', '', '', '2010-04-10 10:36:45', '2010-04-10 14:36:45', '', 608, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/608-revision-10', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2435, 5, '2009-06-17 22:09:20', '2009-06-18 02:09:20', 'In this fast-motion, wide-angle shot of the eclipse in Yiwu, China, in 2008, we can clearly see the shadow of the Moon sweep across the Earth towards us - bathe us in its unearthly light - then sweep away from us at over 3000 kilometers per hour. You rarely get to see umbral action like this! Spine-tingling!', 'Umbral Action!', 0, 'Watch the umbra move across Earth! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '635-revision-5', '', '', '2009-06-17 22:09:20', '2009-06-18 02:09:20', '', 635, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/635-revision-5', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2436, 5, '2009-09-20 18:11:56', '2009-09-20 22:11:56', 'Eclipse in China - 01 August 2008. This is only a preview of the complete film which I have not finished yet! But the eclipse sequence is so dramatic I want to share it now. The clouds that threatened to eclipse the eclipse actually provided an ideal platform under which to observe the full motion of the umbra through the sky. Stunning! Can you spot the lightning on the horizon?  It strikes three times during the eclipse. \r\n\r\nDon\'t miss the time-lapse version of this shot as well, "Umbral Action."\r\n\r\n', 'Shadow On The Silk Road', 0, 'Total Eclipse with lightning on the horizon in China 2008! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '631-revision-8', '', '', '2009-09-20 18:11:56', '2009-09-20 22:11:56', '', 631, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/631-revision-8', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2437, 5, '2009-06-08 15:27:32', '2009-06-08 19:27:32', 'My friend Jim Huddle shot this amazing footage of the Total Eclipse in Antarctica in November 2003. From his location, the eclipse happened right on the horizon making this eclipse unique in the experience of eclipse chasers. I was in Antarctica as well for this one, but at a different location. Together, we were among the first humans to witness a Total Eclipse from Antarctica.', 'Antarctica Total Eclipse 2003', 0, 'It looks fake but this is real!!!!  Totality in Antarctica.  ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '618-revision-6', '', '', '2009-06-08 15:27:32', '2009-06-08 19:27:32', '', 618, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/618-revision-6', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2438, 5, '2009-05-22 22:49:55', '2009-05-23 02:49:55', 'Watch the change in light on the beach as the Moon\'s shadow departs our location at Baby Beach in Aruba in 1998.', 'The Umbra Retreats in Aruba', 0, 'Watch the Umbra retreat in Aruba in 1998.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '614-revision-4', '', '', '2009-05-22 22:49:55', '2009-05-23 02:49:55', '', 614, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/614-revision-4', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2439, 5, '2009-05-22 22:50:45', '2009-05-23 02:50:45', 'The Total Eclipse of 1991 over Hawaii, Mexico and Central America was considered "The Big One" because the duration of totality was one of the longest of the 20th century. This eclipse is also considered to be the one that launched the modern day phenomenon known as "eclipse chasing" when in fact people have been flocking to see Total Solar Eclipses for centuries. Famous Canadian eclipse photographer Andreas Gada shot this 16mm film from Baja California. It don\'t get no betta!!! Sweeeet!!!', 'The Big One 1991', 0, 'Sweet 16mm eclipse film from The Big One!', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '604-revision-5', '', '', '2009-05-22 22:50:45', '2009-05-23 02:50:45', '', 604, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/604-revision-5', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2440, 5, '2011-07-28 16:35:46', '2011-07-28 20:35:46', 'Thanks to NASA\'s public service, these images of the Total Eclipse from Turkey in 1999 show great chromosphere and a few stunning moments of the inner corona.  Check it out!  No audio on this one.', 'Totality in Turkey 1999', 0, 'Great shots of the corona courtesy of NASA! ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '600-revision-6', '', '', '2011-07-28 16:35:46', '2011-07-28 20:35:46', '', 600, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/600-revision-6', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
