(2495, 5, '2012-03-24 23:10:40', '2012-03-25 03:10:40', 'Where will you be?\r\n<h3>2012</h3>\r\n<strong>May 20</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. East China Sea. Japan, N. Pacific. Western U.S.  <a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/news/the-next-eclipse" target="_self">More on this.</a>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2012may20a.gif" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<strong>November 13</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 4:02. N. Australia. Pacific Ocean.  <a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/news/total-eclipse-in-2012" target="_self">More on this. </a>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2012nov13t.gif" alt="" />\r\n<h3>2013</h3>\r\n<strong>May 10</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. N. Australia. Pacific Ocean.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2013may10a.gif" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<strong>November 3</strong> - Hybrid Eclipse (Annular/Total). Atlantic Ocean. Central Africa.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2013nov03h.gif" alt="" />\r\n<h3>2014</h3>\r\n<strong>April 29</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. Australia. Southern Ocean.\r\n\r\n<strong>October 23</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. N. America.\r\n<h3>2015</h3>\r\n<strong>March 20</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 2:47. North Pole. Norwegian Sea.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/SE2015Mar20T.GIF" alt="TSE2015animation" />\r\n<strong>September 13</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. S. Africa. Antarctica.\r\n<h3>2016</h3>\r\n<strong>March 9</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 4:09.  Sumatra, Borneo, Sulawesi, Pacific Ocean.\r\n\r\n<strong>September 1</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse.  Africa.  Indian Ocean.\r\n<h3>2017</h3>\r\n<strong>February 26</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. Pacific. Chile. Argentina. Atlantic. Africa.\r\n\r\n<strong>August 21</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 2:40. United States.', 'Eclipse Calendar', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '551-revision-45', '', '', '2012-03-24 23:10:40', '2012-03-25 03:10:40', '', 551, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/551-revision-45', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2496, 5, '2012-06-11 22:47:16', '2012-06-12 02:47:16', '<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/annularity_thumb.jpg" alt="news annularity 2012" /></p>\r\n\r\n<figure>While thousands of onlookers enjoyed the May 20 annular eclipse from places like the Grand Canyon and Zion National Park, a small team of us ventured to the eclipse path\'s southern limit in Arizona to try to catch a glimpse of the "edge phenomenon" that is only visible during this kind of eclipse.  And what a great idea it was!  See the brand new documentary <a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/video/beads-in-arizona" target="_self">here</a>.</figure>', 'Success In The Desert!', 0, 'Spectacular annular eclipse bedazzles thousands in the American southwest May 20.  \r\nBrand New Documentary Film', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2387-revision-7', '', '', '2012-06-11 22:47:16', '2012-06-12 02:47:16', '', 2387, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/2387-revision-7', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
