(2572, 5, '2012-10-09 17:46:13', '2012-10-09 21:46:13', '<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/being_human_totality.jpg" alt="being human 600" /></p>\r\n\r\n<figure>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">How cool is this?  Gorgeous image.  But can you spot the error in celestial mechanics?</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\r\n</figure>\r\nThe sun would have to be on the horizon to color the clouds like that!  But there it is - hiding behind the Moon above that building!\r\n\r\nA mere technicality.  This image from the tv show "Being Human" is one of a number of awesome eclipse creations used by the producers for their episode "Partial Eclipse of the Heart."\r\n\r\nI\'ve put the <a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/video/solar-eclipses-in-tv-shows">relevant eclipse scenes together here</a> for anyone interested in checking it out!', 'TV producers using eclipses - again. ', 0, 'We\'ve all seen eclipses in film and tv.  But this one is first rate!', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tv-producers-using-eclipses-again', '', '', '2012-11-26 22:44:50', '2012-11-27 02:44:50', '', 0, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/?p=2572', 0, 'post', '', 0),
