r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Partnering with the Universe</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">For 20 years, David Makepeace has travelled the world to witness Total Solar Eclipses - a natural phenomenon that has been called the most spectacular event you can witness from Earth.</p>\r\n"When the shadow of the Moon sweeps over us, we are brought into direct contact with a tangible presence that is awe-inspiring.  That there is a powerful relationship between us and the immense forces of the universe becomes undeniable."\r\n\r\nWhat possible relationship could you have to the universe?  How could it make a difference in your life?\r\n\r\nWith breathtaking film and video captured around the world at eclipse events, Makepeace takes us on a tour of our world and our solar system - widening the perspective on our lives as only an eclipse chaser can.  Discover how the simple beauty and mystery of our world can open the door to a greater awareness of what we are and our place in the universe.', 'Speaking Engagements', 0, 'The Pitchman For The Universe is on tour in 2013.  Come see my inspiring presentation about our place in the universe.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2261-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-03-21 22:35:57', '2013-03-22 02:35:57', '', 2261, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/2261-revision-41', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2760, 5, '2013-07-16 20:34:00', '2013-07-17 00:34:00', '<a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/starfest_talk_600.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2761 aligncenter" alt="starfest_talk_600" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/starfest_talk_600.jpg" width="600" height="400" /></a>\r\n<figure>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Observing the night sky is what this is all about.     Photo: <em>Lukas Gornisiewicz</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\r\n</figure>\r\nI will be presenting a talk on the Eclipse Panel (moderated by Fred Espenak) at 11am on Saturday August 10, 2013.  <a href="http://www.nyaa.ca/index.php?page=sf.directionstostarfest" target="_blank">See map here for directions and details</a>.\r\n\r\n2012 was a great year for eclipse chasing. The Annular Eclipse chase to Arizona in May was a complete success, and the Total Eclipse we saw in Queensland, Australia, in November was simply out of this world. I will talk about both of these incredible events and present original film and video that can\'t be missed!\r\n\r\nStarfest is Canada\'s biggest annual star party -  featuring talks, presentations and workshops with the pros in amateur astronomy, along with vendors of all kinds, all night deep sky observing, and more amazement per mile than Disneyland!  And don\'t forget the Perseid Meteor Shower - at it\'s best Sun Aug 11 and Mon Aug 12 from dusk to dawn.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Come see my talk at Starfest', 0, 'Come see my talk at STARFEST!\r\nSaturday August 10, 2013, in Southern Ontario. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'come-see-my-talk-at-starfest-in-southern-ontario', '', '', '2015-05-05 00:04:10', '2015-05-05 04:04:10', '', 0, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/?p=2760', 0, 'post', '', 0),
