(3263, 5, '2015-06-11 13:51:07', '2015-06-11 17:51:07', 'On this chase I teamed up with Lukas Gornisiewicz - another fine, young Canadian eclipse chaser - and we produced these images together. These photos where taken at 1050m above sea level on Cerro Huyliche - high in the Patagonian steppe - overlooking Lago Argentino to the snow-capped peaks of the distant Andes in the west. You can\'t tell just by looking how frigid the conditions were - below zero - high winds - and two feet of snow. All the predictions said we would not see the eclipse from here. But in stark contrast to this, nothing, it seems, could stop it from being seen. It was miraculous and stunning.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/image_3.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3260" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/image_3.jpg" alt="image_3" width="1000" height="667" /></a> <a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/image_2.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3261" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/image_2.jpg" alt="image_2" width="1000" height="667" /></a> <a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/image_1.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3262" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/image_1.jpg" alt="image_1" width="1000" height="667" /></a>', 'Total Solar Eclipse in Patagonia 11 July 2010', 0, 'Only three shots in this collection - but they are good ones!  You won\'t see eclipse shots like these anywhere else.  ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1804-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-11 13:51:07', '2015-06-11 17:51:07', '', 1804, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/1804-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3264, 5, '2010-08-01 17:09:15', '2010-08-01 21:09:15', 'The Best-Laid Plans...\r\n\r\nWe were so lucky.  With the 11th hour cancellation of my eclipse flight to see totality at 35,000 I thought I was going to miss my first total eclipse in 19 years.  But no.  From the Andes Mountains around El Calafate in southern Patagonia - overlooking Lago Argentino - I witnessed a truly inspiring sight:  the eclipse - hovering like a cosmic jewel over snow-capped peaks.  Read the complete trip report <a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/tripreport/south-america-%E2%80%93-11-july-2010">here.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://eclipseguy.dev/video/raw-video-from-patagonia-11-july-2010-2">See the Raw Video here.</a>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/worldmap_calafate.jpg" alt="" /></p>', 'Raw Video from Patagonia - 11 July 2010', 0, 'My eclipse observation flight at 35,000 feet never happened.  But from the ground, the eclipse was spectacular.  See the NEW VIDEO!', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1785-revision-v1', '', '', '2010-08-01 17:09:15', '2010-08-01 21:09:15', '', 1785, 'http://eclipseguy.dev/1785-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
